<li id="cite_note-37"><b><a href="#cite_ref-37" title="">^</a></b> "Suddenly I became aware that an <a href="/wiki/Adenine" title="Adenine">adenine</a>-<a href="/wiki/Thymine" title="Thymine">thymine</a> pair held together by two <a href="/wiki/Hydrogen_bond" title="Hydrogen bond">hydrogen bonds</a> was identical in shape to a <a href="/wiki/Guanine" title="Guanine">guanine</a>-<a href="/wiki/Cytosine" title="Cytosine">cytosine</a> pair held together by at least two hydrogen bonds. ..." —<a href="#CITEREFWatson1968" title="">Watson 1968</a>, pp.&#160;194-197.</li>
